{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place almond pulp, 20 g reserved grated Parmesan, rosemary, flaxseed, bicarbonate of soda, garlic powder and salt then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Without measuring cup, mix <b>1 min\/speed 1<b> while slowly adding olive oil through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then, without measuring cup, mix <b>1 min\/speed 1<b> while adding 2-3 Tbsp water, until mixture comes together into a moist dough.","Transfer dough to a bowl, shape into a ball, cover with cling film and place in fridge for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 190°C.","Transfer chilled dough to a sheet of baking paper, then cover with another sheet of baking paper. Roll dough out to a large rectangle (approx. 3 mm thick), then remove top sheet of paper and use a sharp knife to score dough into 25 - 30 rectangular crackers (approx. 5 cm x 4 cm).","Lift up baking paper with crackers on and transfer to a baking tray. Sprinkle crackers with remaining grated Parmesan, then prick each cracker twice with a fork.","Bake for 15 minutes (190°C). Using a spatula, carefully separate crackers and flip over, then bake for a further 10-15 minutes (190°C) until edges of crackers are golden brown.","Leave crackers to cool on baking tray then transfer to an airtight container and store until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","180 - 200 g almond pulp, leftover from homemade almond milk (see tip)","2 sprigs fresh rosemary, needles only, finely chopped","2 tsp ground flaxseed","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 tsp garlic powder","½ tsp fine sea salt","2 Tbsp olive oil","2 - 3 Tbsp water"]}],"id":"r278228","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-6t0xEdX30rY\/XZaq4BA0XOI\/AAAAAAAAhiE\/_xencLFEl6wLN1dPBwbLZoVKvWocQbsRwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_roVCmuCiDvD7-iOA.png","title":"Rosemary a